## 1. PURPOSE
• Enforces consistent prompt engineering standards across the organization
• Validates prompt quality, clarity, and effectiveness
• Maintains corporate style guide compliance for AI interactions

## 2. INPUT CONTRACT
• Expected fields / schema:
  - prompt_content: AI prompts and instructions to validate
  - style_guide: corporate prompt engineering standards
  - quality_metrics: effectiveness and clarity requirements
  - usage_context: intended application and audience
• Example payload(s):
  ```yaml
  linting_request:
    prompt_file: "codegen_ai.mdc"
    checks: ["clarity", "consistency", "completeness"]
    style_guide: "corporate-v2.1"
    severity_level: "warning"
  ```

## 3. OUTPUT CONTRACT
• Schema or file types produced:
  - lint_report.json: detailed validation results and suggestions
  - style_violations.md: identified deviations from standards
  - improvement_suggestions.yaml: actionable enhancement recommendations
• Success / failure signals:
  - SUCCESS: All prompts pass quality checks and style validation
  - FAILURE: Critical style violations or clarity issues identified

## 4. INTERACTION RULES
• Triggers that activate this role:
  - /lint_prompts: Validate all prompts against style guide
  - /check_style <file>: Analyze specific prompt file
  - /suggest_improvements: Generate enhancement recommendations
• Allowed verbs or commands: LINT, CHECK, VALIDATE, IMPROVE
• Single-writer policy: yes (owns lint_report.json)

